                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="a1">
                                    <desc type="Condemnation"/>
                                    <locus target="#51v">f. 51v </locus>
                                    <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                                    <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                                    <p>The note excommunicates whoever sells the book for starvation or poverty and whoever steals it.</p>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="a2">
                                    <desc type="OwnershipNote"/>
                                    <locus target="#51v">f. 51v </locus>
                                    <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                                    <quote xml:lang="en">"This book belongs to Kǝsāda Qāl, whose wife is Birut Ḥāwit, whose father is ʾAfa Krǝstos, and whose mother is .... The scribe is Tābor".</quote>
                                    <p>The note states that the book belongs to <persName ref="https://www.betamasaheft.uni-hamburg.de/PRS10769KesadaQ"/>. His wife <persName ref="https://www.betamasaheft.uni-hamburg.de/PRS10770BirutH"/> and his father <persName ref="https://www.betamasaheft.uni-hamburg.de/PRS10771AfaKre"/> are also mentioned. The note also mentions <persName ref="https://www.betamasaheft.uni-hamburg.de/PRS10768Tabor"/> as the scribe.</p> 
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="a3">
                                    <desc type="ScribalNoteCompleting"/>
                                    <locus target="#137r">f. 137r </locus>
                                    <quote xml:lang="gez">ተፈጸመ፡ ዘዕዝራ፡ ፫ ወተጽሕፈት፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዕዝራ። ዘአጽሐፈኒ፡ ... ወጸሓፊሁ፡ መልከ፡ ጼዴቅ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ ለተዝካሩ፡ ወለተዝካረ፡ ደቂቁ፡ ወይዕቀቦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ እምኵሉ፡ እኩይ፡ ወያኑኅ፡ መዋዕሊሁ፡ በዲበ፡ ምድር፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ለይኩን፡ ለኩን።</quote>
                                    <quote xml:lang="en">"Ezra 3 is finished, and this book of Ezra has been written. The one who commissioned me is ..., and its scribe is Malka Ṣedeq. Shall his memory and the memory of his sons be commemorated, and may God protect him from any evil and make his days long on the Earth, forever and ever, amen, amen. So be it, so be it".</quote>
                                    <p>The note follows <ref target="#ms_i4"/>. It mentions <persName ref="https://www.betamasaheft.uni-hamburg.de/PRS10772MalkaS"/> as the scribe. The Book of Ezra and Nehemiah is here labelled Ezra 3, according to the Ethiopian numbering.</p>
                                    <listBibl type="text">
                                        <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/4X2S93BV" type="book">
                                 <title level="m">Le troisième livre de 'Ezra (Esdras et Néhémie canoniques). Version éthiopienne</title>
